{SECT 0 {EXCHG {PARA 205 "" 0 "" {TEXT 228 26 "Dynamic Equations For T
he " }}{PARA 206 "" 0 "" {TEXT 229 59 "First Stage Of The 2-DOF Serial
 Flexible Link (2DSFL) Robot" }}{PARA 207 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 1 "\251" }
{TEXT 230 29 " 2008 Quanser Consulting Inc." }}{PARA 208 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 231 5 "URL: " }{HYPERLNK 232 "http://www.quanser.com" 4 "www.qua
nser.com" "" }}}{PARA 209 "" 0 "Description" }{SECT 0 {PARA 210 "" 0 "
" {TEXT 233 11 "Description" }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 166 "This w
orksheet presents the general dynamic equations modelling the First St
age Of Quanser's 2-DOF Serial Flexible Link (2DSFL) Robot, assuming a \+
decoupled modelling." }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 83 "This worksheet
 derives the state-space matrices used in the control implementation."
 }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 72 "The Lagrange's method is used to ob
tain the dynamic model of the system." }}{SECT 0 {PARA 212 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 235 4 "The " }{TEXT 236 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT 235 8 " Packag
e" }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 4 "The " }{TEXT 237 13 "Quanser_Tools
" }{TEXT 234 228 " module defines generic procedures and data in relat
ion to determining the state-space representation of all the Quanser e
xperiments. Specifically, this means deriving and solving the Lagrange
's equations of the Quanser systems." }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 4 
"The " }{TEXT 237 7 "quanser" }{TEXT 234 27 " repository containing th
e " }{TEXT 237 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT 234 50 " package is implement
ed in the 2 following files: " }{TEXT 237 11 "quanser.ind" }{TEXT 234 
5 " and " }{TEXT 237 12 "quanser.lib." }{TEXT 234 110 " If these two f
iles are not readily available, they can be generated by executing the
 Maple worksheet titled: " }{TEXT 237 17 "quanser_tools.mws" }{TEXT 
234 1 "." }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 10 "To install" }{TEXT 234 5 "
 the " }{TEXT 237 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT 234 29 " package, copy the
 two files " }{TEXT 237 11 "quanser.ind" }{TEXT 234 5 " and " }{TEXT 
237 11 "quanser.lib" }{TEXT 234 98 "  into a directory of your choice,
 like for example: \"C:\\Program Files\\Quanser\\Maple Repository\". "
 }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 6 "To use" }{TEXT 234 5 " the " }{TEXT 
237 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT 234 94 " package in a Maple worksheet, a
dd the path to its disk location to the Maple global variable " }
{TEXT 237 7 "libname" }{TEXT 234 68 ". For example, this can be achiev
ed by the following Maple command: " }{TEXT 234 12 "\nlibname := " }
{TEXT 237 54 " \"C:/Program Files/Quanser/Maple Repository\", libname:
" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 210 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 24 "Worksheet Initialization
" }}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 41 "restart: interface( \+
imaginaryunit = j ): " }}}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 
22 "with( LinearAlgebra ):" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
239 69 "libname := \"C:/Program Files/Quanser/Maple Repository\", \".
\", libname:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 22 "with( Q
uanser_Tools );" }}{PARA 214 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#7,%$HTMG%(deriveAG
%(deriveBG%(deriveFG%/kinetic_energyG%3lagrange_equationsG%2moment_of_
inertiaG%'n_normG%1potential_energyG%4write_ABCD_to_MfileG" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 66 "environment variable representing the \+
order of series calculations" }}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 11 
"Order := 2:" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 210 "" 0 "Notations" {TEXT 233 9 "Nota
tions" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 212 "" 0 "" {TEXT 235 25 "Generalized Coordinat
es: " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "q[i]" "6#&%\"qG6#%\"iG" }{TEXT 235 2 "'s" }}
{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 67 "The generalized coordinates are also c
alled Lagrangian coordinates." }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {XPPEDIT 18 0 "thet
a[11](t);" "6#-&%&thetaG6#\"#66#%\"tG" }{TEXT 240 110 " =  driving sha
ft (of harmonic drive #1) angular position: the zero angle is defined \+
as the starting position." }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {XPPEDIT 18 0 "theta[12
](t);" "6#-&%&thetaG6#\"#76#%\"tG" }{TEXT 240 107 " = first link (abso
lute) end-effector angular position: the zero angle is defined as the \+
starting position." }}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 36 "q \+
:= [ theta[11](t), theta[12](t) ];" }}{PARA 216 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6
#>%\"qG7$-&%&thetaG6#\"#66#%\"tG-&F(6#\"#7F+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0
 "" {TEXT 240 63 "Nq = number of Lagrangian coordinates (e.g. here, it
 is Nq = 2)" }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 41 "Nq is also the number o
f position states." }}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 16 "Nq := nop
s( q ):" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 101 "qd = first-order t
ime derivative of the generalized coordinates, e.g. position and angul
ar velocities" }}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 24 "qd := map( dif
f, q, t );" }}{PARA 216 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#qdG7$-%%diffG6$-&%&t
hetaG6#\"#66#%\"tGF/-F'6$-&F+6#\"#7F.F/" }}}}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" }{SECT 
0 {PARA 212 "" 0 "" {TEXT 235 21 "State-Space Variables" }}{PARA 211 "
" 0 "" {TEXT 234 103 "The chosen states should at least include the ge
neralized coordinates and their first-time derivatives." }}{PARA 211 "
" 0 "" {TEXT 234 22 "X is the state vector." }}{PARA 211 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 234 141 "In the state vector X: Lagrangian coordinates are first
, followed by their first-time derivatives, and finally any other stat
es, as required." }}{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 78 "Substitutio
n sets for the states (to obtain time-independent state equations)." }
}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 43 "subs_Xq := \{ seq( q[i] = X[i]
, i=1..Nq ) \};" }{MPLTEXT 1 239 49 "\nsubs_Xqd := \{ seq( qd[i] = X[i
+Nq], i=1..Nq ) \};" }}{PARA 216 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%(subs_XqG<$/
-&%&thetaG6#\"#66#%\"tG&%\"XG6#\"\"\"/-&F)6#\"#7F,&F/6#\"\"#" }}{PARA 
216 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%)subs_XqdG<$/-%%diffG6$-&%&thetaG6#\"#66#
%\"tGF0&%\"XG6#\"\"$/-F(6$-&F,6#\"#7F/F0&F26#\"\"%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 34 "Substitution set for the input(s)." }}{PARA 
215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 41 "set the input to be the motor #1 current:" }
}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 27 "subs_U := \{ I[m1] = U[1] \}:"
 }}}{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 109 "set the input to be the ac
tuator driving force/torque (if not expressed as a function of the mot
or voltage): " }}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 27 "#subs_U := \{ \+
T[1] = U[1] \}:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 66 "Nu = number
 of inputs; U = input (row) vector (e.g. U = [ V[m] ] )" }}{PARA 213 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 21 "Nu := nops( subs_U ):" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 65 "substitution set for the position states' se
cond time derivatives" }}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 63 "subs_X
qdd := \{ seq( diff( q[i], t$2 ) =  Xd[i+Nq], i=1..Nq ) \};" }}{PARA 
216 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%*subs_XqddG<$/-%%diffG6$-&%&thetaG6#\"#66
#%\"tG-%\"$G6$F0\"\"#&%#XdG6#\"\"$/-F(6$-&F,6#\"#7F/F1&F66#\"\"%" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 87 "second time derivatives of the \+
position states (written as time-independent variables)." }}{PARA 215 
"" 0 "" {TEXT 240 91 "The set of unknowns is obtained from this list t
o solve the Lagrange's equations of motion." }}{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 239 37 "Xqdd := [ seq( Xd[i+Nq], i=1..Nq ) ];" }}{PARA 216 
"" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%%XqddG7$&%#XdG6#\"\"$&F'6#\"\"%" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 70 "substitution set to linearize the stat
e-space matrices (i.e. A and B) " }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 65 "ab
out the quiescent null state vector (small-displacement theory)" }}
{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 72 "subs_XUzero := \{ seq( X[i] = 0
, i=1..2*Nq ), seq( U[i] = 0, i=1..Nu ) \}:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0 
"" {TEXT 240 83 "Nx = dim( X ) = total number of states (should be gre
ater than or equal to: 2 * Nq)" }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 29 "Ny =
 chosen number of outputs" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
239 17 "Nx := 2 * Nq + 0:" }{MPLTEXT 1 239 10 "\nNy := Nq:" }}}}}
{SECT 0 {PARA 210 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 50 "Total Potential and Kinetic En
ergies of the System" }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 94 "The total pote
ntial and kinetic energies are needed to calculate the Lagrangian of t
he system." }}{SECT 0 {PARA 212 "" 0 "" {TEXT 235 24 "Total Potential \+
Energy: " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "V[T];" "6#&%\"VG6#%\"TG" }{TEXT 235 1 " " }}
{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 90 "The total potential energy can be expr
essed in terms of the generalized coordinates alone." }}{EXCHG {PARA 
215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 58 "Vg[T] = Total Gravitational Potential Energy
 of the system" }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 74 "Vg[T] = 0 : Because \+
the load vertical displacement from normality is null." }}{PARA 213 ">
 " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 12 "Vg[T] := 0: " }}}{EXCHG {PARA 215 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 240 52 "Ve[T] = Total Elastic Potential Energy of the system" }
{TEXT 240 48 "\nK[s1] = first flexible link torsional stiffness" }}
{PARA 213 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 51 "Ve[T] := potential_energy( 'spr
ing', K[s1], q[2] );" }}{PARA 216 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%#VeG6#%\"T
