nertia (or mass) Matrix: Fi" }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 118 "The no
nlinear system of equations resulting from the Lagrangian mechanics ca
n be written in the following matrix form:" }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
240 59 "F( q ) . qdd + G( q, qd ) . qd + H( q ) . q = L( q, qd, u )" }
}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 240 80 "F, G, and H are called, respectively,
 the mass, damping, and stiffness matrices." }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 240 27 "They are symmetric in form." }}{PARA 215 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
240 101 "The inertia (a.k.a. mass) matrix, F, gives indications regard
ing the coupling existing in the system." }}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 0 ""
 {MPLTEXT 1 239 23 "Fi := Matrix( Nq, Nq ):" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 213 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 239 21 "for i from 1 to Nq do" }{MPLTEXT 1 239 24 "\n \+
 for k from 1 to Nq do" }{MPLTEXT 1 239 72 "\n    Fi[ i, k ] := simpli
fy( diff( op( 1, EOM_states[i] ), Xd[k+Nq] ) );" }{MPLTEXT 1 239 63 "
\n    Fi[ i, k ] := collect( combine( Fi[ i, k ], trig ), cos );" }
{MPLTEXT 1 239 10 "\n  end do;" }{MPLTEXT 1 239 8 "\nend do:" }}}
